<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="16" pageNumber="31" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="16" pageNumber="31">
<bibRefCitation pageId="16" pageNumber="31">Fet and Lowe (2000)</bibRefCitation>
considered the locality as probably wrong since at that time no other 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="16" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
had been collected again in Yemen. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco, WR" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg" pageId="30" pageNumber="45" pagination="45 - 52" title="About the presence of the genus Buthus Leach, 1815 in the Arabian Peninsula and description of a new species (Scorpiones, Buthidae)." volume="15" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lourenço's">Lourenco's</normalizedToken>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus yemenensis" order="Scorpiones" pageId="16" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yemenensis">Buthus yemenensis</taxonomicName>
revalidated Ehrenberg 
<normalizedToken originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
by providing concrete proof 
<pageBreakToken pageId="17" pageNumber="32" start="start">for</pageBreakToken>
the existence of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
species in this country. Doubst about 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. intermedius" pageId="17" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="intermedius">B. intermedius</taxonomicName>
type locality were the only evidence given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovarik, F" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="29" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 16" title="Review of Tunisian Species of the Genus Buthus with Descriptions of Two New Species and a Discussion of Ehrenberg's Types (Scorpiones: Buthidae)." url="http://www.science.marshall.edu/fet/euscorpius/p2006_34.pdf" volume="34" year="2006">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kovařík">Kovarik</normalizedToken>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
for its synonimization with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus intumescens" order="Scorpiones" pageId="17" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intumescens">Buthus intumescens</taxonomicName>
(Ehrenberg in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hemprich, FW" journalOrPublisher="Verhandungen der Gessellschaft naturforschende Freunde in Berlin" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" pagination="348 - 362" title="Vorlaeufige Uebersicht der in Nord-Afrika und West-Asien einheimischen Scorpione und deren geographischen Verbreitung, nach den eigenen Beobachtungen von Dr. Hemprich und Dr. Ehrenberg." url="https://books.google.pt/books?id=8OoTAAAAQAAJ" volume="1" year="1829">Hemprich and Ehrenberg 1829</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
